    <stitle>10 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS EATON RTLO SERIES - REMOVE - AUXILIARY SECTION WITHOUT TAPERED BEARINGS</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="5">
        <title>AUXILIARY SECTION WITHOUT TAPERED BEARINGS</title>
        <svcprocinfo>
            <para>There can be different bolt lengths; note their location.</para>
            <para>Auxiliary sections can be removed either with the transmission in the horizontal position or the
                vertical position.
            </para>
        </svcprocinfo>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>To remove the auxiliary section in the horizontal position.</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the retaining bolts that attach the front section to the auxiliary section (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1301722">Figure 22</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <figure id="f1301722" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g1301722" filename="../figg13/G1301722.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 22. Remove Retaining Bolts</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Insert the two (2) longest bolts in the housing flange tapped holes. Tighten evenly to
                    move the auxiliary section away from the front box. Go far enough to break the gasket seal (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1301723">Figure 23</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <figure id="f1301723" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g1301723" filename="../figg13/G1301723.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 23. Break Gasket Seal</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the bolts from the tapped holes.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Attach an auxiliary section hanger bracket to the top of the auxiliary section (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1301724">Figure 24</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <figure id="f1301724" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g1301724" filename="../figg13/G1301724.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 24. Attach Lifting Chain</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Attach a lifting chain to the auxiliary section hanger bracket (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1301724">Figure 24</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Move assembly to the rear until auxiliary section is free.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the gasket and clean all mounting surfaces of gasket material (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1301724">Figure 24</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>To remove the auxiliary section in the vertical position.</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">With blocks under the clutch housing to prevent input shaft damage, place transmission
                    in the vertical position.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the retaining bolts that attach auxiliary section to the front section (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1301725">Figure 25</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <figure id="f1301725" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g1301725" filename="../figg13/G1301725.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 25. Remove Retaining Bolts</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install a steel bar through the yoke (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1301726">Figure 26</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <figure id="f1301726" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g1301726" filename="../figg13/G1301726.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 26. Install Bar Through Yoke</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Attach a lifting chain to the steel bar (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1301726">Figure 26</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Lift assembly from the front section.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the gasket and clean all mounting surfaces of gasket material.</para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
